node.text:
Surfing is one of the few activities left in your routine that requires you to operate fully in the moment.
When you're out there, you're detached from the usual distractions of life on land. 
Seemingly every other form of recreation and leisure has been tainted by the attention-splitting, ever-present cell phone.  But thankfully the ocean strips that option away. 
Even if they invent fully waterproof phones, riding a wave requires 100% of your attention. The primary aim of surfing, after all, is to read what the wave is doing and respond in kind.  It's like playing ping-pong against an unbeaten foe.  The ocean will keep throwing looks and you, and you've got to do your best to respond. Photo: @jeffrey_allee #twofeetandfiring #earlyandoftensurfclub

node.text: New Deck Pad alert! We have some very fun new color ways coming to your favorite foamie surfboards—the Navy Nautical Chart and the Orange Peel. We’re just injecting some late Summer color into the boards that inject year-round fun into your quiver.  They aren’t a available for purchase just yet, but you can go to our website, find the one you like, and be notified as soon as it becomes available for ordering. Kind of like a front of the line pass. Big thank you to @amyhoodlum of @hoodzpahdesign for lending her delightful talents to us for the Orange Peel design. Amy is also the designer of the ever-popular California Surf Checklist poster in the shop. Excited for these new additions to the R-Series range. We’re always working behind the scenes on something new, so stay tuned. 🙏 thanks friends. #rseriesbyalmond
